add_account_button_text.description: Text for the Add Account button. Directs the user to a page where they can sign into a google account

admin_install_required_text.description: Text shown for ADMIN_INSTALL_REQUIRED. On ChromeOS devices only, the extension must be force installed on the device by the Google Workspace administrator who manages the device. See https://support.google.com/chrome/a/answer/6306504 for more context
admin_install_required_text.message: This extension must be force installed by the enterprise admin on ChromeOS.

bce_api_helper_download_button.description: Text shown on the API helper download button.

bce_api_helper_download_prompt.description: Text shown to ask user to download and install API Helper.
bce_api_helper_download_prompt.message: Download and install BeyondCorp Enterprise native helper.

bce_certificate_install_notification.description: Text shown to the user in Chrome notification body for certificate install.
bce_certificate_install_notification.message: Your admin has updated Proxy certificates. A browser restart maybe required after certificate installation.

bce_certificate_management_failure_text.description: Text shown to the user if certificate install failed.
bce_certificate_management_failure_text.message: Failed to install certificates. A sync will be retried shortly. Please contact your enterprise administrator if the issue continues.

bce_empty_proxy_list.description: Text shown to the user when tenant config is empty.

bce_initial_sync_promt.description: Text shown to perform the first sync that may install certificates.
bce_initial_sync_promt.message: Sync now to install CA certificates.

bce_proxy_auth_generic_error.description: Text shown to the user when authentication with proxy fails.
bce_proxy_auth_generic_error.message: BeyondCorp Extension encountered an error while authenticating with the Proxy. A sync will be retried shortly. Please contact your enterprise administrator if the issue persists.

bce_restart_prompt.description: Text shown to ask user to restart the browser.
bce_restart_prompt.message: Restart the browser. Please visit chrome://restart to restart.

bce_signin_prompt.description: Text shown when no accounts are logged in. Users must be signed in with a google account.
bce_signin_prompt.message: requires you to be logged into your work account.

bce_sync_additional_info.description: Additional test to shown to the user after a sync.
bce_sync_additional_info.message: You can now access your enterprise applications.

bce_sync_button_text.description: Text on the sync button. 'Sync', both here and in other messages, refers to syncing the latest proxy configuration from the server.

bce_sync_failure_text.description: Text shown to the user if a configuration sync failed.
bce_sync_failure_text.message: Failed to sync. A sync will be retried shortly. Please contact your enterprise administrator if the issue persists.

clear_log.description: Text for a title of the clear log button

consent_more_details.description: Continuation of the 'consent_text' message. 'Details' means more information regarding the Google Privacy Policy

consent_more_details_link.description: Continuation of the 'consent_more_details' message. It is separate because this text will be turned into a clickable link to a separate information page.

consent_text.description: The consent message shown to the user.
consent_text.message: Your enterprise administrator is protecting this device with

data_integrity_error_text.message: Can't sync because of a data integrity error. Reenrolling the device through a manual sync might resolve the issue.

data_protection_key_error_text.message: Failed to recover data protection key.

disabled_accounts.description: Text shown for the list of disabled accounts. Refers to accounts which the user is signed into but have not been enabled by the domain administrator
disabled_accounts.message: These accounts are not enabled for

download_log.description: Text for a button that downloads the extension log file to the user's machine

dpapi_failure_error_text.description: Text shown for DPAPI related errors on Windows only.
dpapi_failure_error_text.message: Can't sync because of a Data Protection API error.

explanation.description: Explanation of the extension. The extension collects device information such as OS information (the operating system, os version number), identifiers (serial number, mac address), and the user using the device. This information is collected and may be viewed in the Google Workspace Admin console by a Google Workspace administrator
explanation.message: allows Google Workspace administrators to view laptop and desktop status, including OS, device, and user information.

extension_description.description: Description of the extension that displays in the Chrome Web Store. Essentially the same as 'explanation_internal' message
extension_description.message: Allows Google Workspace administrators to view laptop and desktop status, including OS, device, and user information.

force_sync.description: Text for a button that forces a sync

get_auth_token_error_text.description: Error text shown when getAuthToken API fails.
get_auth_token_error_text.message: Unable to authenticate, please make sure you are signed into your account and try again.

get_help_link_text.description: Text shown for troubleshooting help article link.

keychain_auth_error_text.description: Text shown for Keychain authorization errors on MacOS only.
keychain_auth_error_text.message: Can't sync because of a Keychain authorization error.

keychain_locked_error_text.description: Text shown for Keychain locked errors on MacOS only.
keychain_locked_error_text.message: Can't sync because the keychain is locked.

last_sync_date.description: Text shown in popup when all accounts have synced at least once. Will be displayed along with a date: i.e. 'Last sync: 07/24/2018 12:00:00'

log_level_label.description: Label for the Log Level combo box on the options page

native_messaging_download_text.description: Text shown as a Native Helper download link.

native_messaging_error_text_1.description: First part of the text shown for NATIVE_MESSAGING_UNAVAILABLE. 'Native Helper' here and in other messages refers to a native binary that must be installed along with the extension in order for the extension to function properly.
native_messaging_error_text_1.message: Required components are missing on this machine. Please

native_messaging_error_text_1_chrome.description: First part of the text shown for NATIVE_MESSAGING_UNAVAILABLE. 'Native Helper' here and in other messages refers to a native binary that must be installed along with the extension in order for the extension to function properly.
native_messaging_error_text_1_chrome.message: Required components are missing on this machine. Please either update Chrome to the latest version or

native_messaging_error_text_2.description: Second part of the text shown for NATIVE_MESSAGING_UNAVAILABLE. 'Native Helper' here and in other messages refers to a native binary that must be installed along with the extension in order for the extension to function properly.
native_messaging_error_text_2.message: and install the Native Helper package.

network_failure_text.description: Text shown for NETWORK_FAILURE. 'Sync' here means sending device information to our server. The message means that we were unable to send the information due to device being offline
network_failure_text.message: Last sync failed due to no network connection.

no_sync_date.description: Text shown in popup when some account has not been synced before

options_page_title_external.description: Title of the external version of the options page

options_page_title_internal.description: Title of the internal version of the options page

platform_keys_inaccessible_text.description: Text shown for PLATFORM_KEYS_INACCESSIBLE. 'Client certificates' and 'keys' here refer cryptographic keys and certificates used to establish secure internet connections. On ChromeOS devices, the extension requires a specific setting to be enabled in order to be able to use these
platform_keys_inaccessible_text.message: The extension needs access to client certificates and keys on ChromeOS.

proxy_uncontrolled_text.description: Text shown to the user when proxy control has been lost by the extension.
proxy_uncontrolled_text.message: BeyondCorp Proxy is unable to apply proxy settings. This may happen if there are other extensions managing the browser's proxy settings.

real_time_log.description: Text for a title of the real time log view

show_log.description: Text for a button that opens the extension log window

signin_prompt.description: Text shown when no accounts are logged in. Users must be signed in with a google account on a domain that has SecureConnect enabled (typically a work or school account)
signin_prompt.message: requires you to be logged into your work or school account.

sync_button_text.description: Text on the sync button. 'Sync', both here and in other messages, refers to sending device information to our server

sync_error_text.description: Text shown for GENERIC_FAILURE. 'Sync' here means sending device information to our server. The message means that we were unable to send the information and will attempt to try again shortly
sync_error_text.message: Failed to sync. A sync will be retried shortly.

title_external.description: The external name of the extension

title_internal.description: The internal (googlers-only) name of the extension

troubleshooting_section_title.description: Title for the 'troubleshooting' section of the options page

vpn_adapter_error_text.description: Error text shown when VPN adapter has failed for any reason.
vpn_adapter_error_text.message: There was a network failure preventing the connection from functioning properly.

vpn_auth_verification_failed_text.description: Error text shown when VPN server rejects the authentication credential.
vpn_auth_verification_failed_text.message: Access to your enterprise network was denied. Please contact your enterprise administrator to resolve the issue.

vpn_connected_banner_text.description: Text for the banner when VPN connection is on.
vpn_connected_banner_text.message: You are connected to your enterprise network.

vpn_connecting_banner_text.description: Text for the banner when VPN connection is being established.

vpn_connection_reset_text.description: Error text shown when the VPN connection has been reset.
vpn_connection_reset_text.message: The connection has been reset. Please wait while the connection is being restored.

vpn_connection_timed_out_text.description: Error text shown when the VPN connection has failed.
vpn_connection_timed_out_text.message: The connection has timed out. Please check your network configuration and make sure you are connected to the Internet.

vpn_connection_tls_error_text.description: Error text shown when a TLS session can't be established. Likely because of a wrong certificate.
vpn_connection_tls_error_text.message: Unable to establish a TLS connection. Please contact your enterprise administrator to resolve the issue.

vpn_disconnected_banner_text.description: Text for the banner when VPN connection is available and off.
vpn_disconnected_banner_text.message: You can connect to your enterprise network to enable certain applications.

vpn_generic_error_text.description: Error text shown when VPN connection fails for any other reason.
vpn_generic_error_text.message: The connection to the remote server has failed. Please try reconnecting or contact your enterprise administrator to resolve the issue.

vpn_network_not_available_text.description: Error text shown when internet connection on client's device is not available.
vpn_network_not_available_text.message: Unable to connect to the network. Check your network connection and try again.
